# FacadeLens — Cursor Rules

You are building FacadeLens: a React Native (Expo bare workflow) mobile app that uses AI to identify and critique architectural elements in building facade photos. Think iNaturalist for architecture.

Read the full product spec at `facadelens-roadmap/ROADMAP.md` and the relevant milestone brief before writing any code for that milestone.

---

## Project Identity

- App name: FacadeLens
- Platform: iOS + Android (React Native, Expo bare workflow)
- Architecture: New Architecture enabled (Fabric + JSI)
- Primary audience: architecture students and curious urbanists
- Aesthetic: premium, dark, architectural — warm gold accent, minimal chrome

---

## Tech Stack (do not deviate)

| Layer | Package |
|---|---|
| Framework | React Native + Expo (bare) |
| Routing | Expo Router (file-based) |
| UI | Tamagui |
| Animation | react-native-reanimated v3 |
| Loading animations | lottie-react-native |
| Icons | phosphor-react-native (primary), @tabler/icons-react-native (secondary) |
| Camera | react-native-vision-camera v4 |
| SVG / overlay | react-native-svg |
| State | Zustand |
| Backend | Supabase (PostgreSQL + PostGIS + Storage + Edge Functions) |
| AI | Google Gemini 2.5 Flash via Edge Function |

**Never introduce new packages without flagging it. Never use expo-camera — always use react-native-vision-camera.**

