## Phosphor Icons Rules

- Always specify `weight` prop — default is `regular`; use `duotone` for accent icons, `fill` for active states
- Always specify `size` prop — never rely on defaults
- Standard sizes: 12 (inline), 16 (UI labels), 20 (buttons), 24 (navigation), 32+ (empty states)
- Standard colors:
  - Active / accent: `'#c8a96e'` (warm gold)
  - Default UI: `'#888880'` (muted)
  - Destructive: `'#c96e6e'`
  - Success: `'#6bc96e'`
- Never pass Tamagui tokens to icon `color` prop — use literal strings

```tsx
// Correct
<Camera size={24} color="#c8a96e" weight="duotone" />

// Wrong
<Camera size={24} color="$accent" />  // tokens don't work here
```

---

## Reanimated Rules

- All animation values are `useSharedValue` — never `useAnimatedValue` (old API)
- All animated styles are `useAnimatedStyle` — never `Animated.Value.interpolate`
- Wrap native components with `Animated.createAnimatedComponent` before animating props
- For entrance/exit animations, use `entering` / `exiting` props on `Animated.View` with Reanimated presets (`FadeIn`, `SlideInDown`, etc.)
- Worklet rule: any function called inside `useAnimatedStyle` or a gesture handler's `onUpdate`/`onEnd` must be a worklet (add `'worklet'` directive or wrap with `runOnJS` for non-worklet calls)
- Stagger delays: 80ms per item for label animations, 100ms per section for critique

---

## Supabase Rules

- Always use the Supabase client from `lib/supabase.ts` — never instantiate a new client
- RLS is always on — never use service role key on the client side
- Service role key is Edge Function only
- All database operations must handle the `{ data, error }` tuple — never ignore the error
- Use `.select('*')` only when you need all fields; prefer explicit field lists for performance
- Image paths in Storage follow the pattern: `{user_id}/{uuid}.jpg`
- Signed URLs expire in 3600 seconds (1 hour) — cache them in component state, don't re-request on every render

---

## Vision Camera Rules

- Always check `hasPermission` before rendering `<Camera>`
- Always check `device` is not null/undefined before rendering `<Camera>`
- Camera ref type: `useRef<Camera>(null)`
- `takePhoto()` returns a `PhotoFile` with a `path` property (local file URI)
- `focus()` takes `{ x, y }` in view coordinates — use gesture handler tap coordinates
- Zoom: bind a Reanimated `useSharedValue` to the `zoom` prop via `useAnimatedProps`
- Never call `takePhoto()` if camera is not active

---

## State Management (Zustand)

- One store per domain: `authStore`, `herbariumStore`, `scanStore`
- Stores live in `stores/` directory
- Always define the full state interface before the store
- Selectors: always use selector functions, not destructuring: `const session = useAuthStore(s => s.session)`
- Never put derived state in stores — compute it in components or hooks

---

## Error Handling Patterns

- User-facing errors: show Tamagui `Toast` or inline error `Text` — never `Alert.alert` (looks native/ugly)
- Network errors: always offer a retry action
- Supabase errors: log to console in development; send to Sentry in production
- Never swallow errors silently with empty catch blocks
- Loading states: every async operation must have a corresponding loading boolean in state

```tsx
// Pattern for async operations
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)
const [error, setError] = useState<string | null>(null)

const handleAction = async () => {
  setLoading(true)
  setError(null)
  try {
    await doSomething()
  } catch (err) {
    setError(err instanceof Error ? err.message : 'Something went wrong')
  } finally {
    setLoading(false)
  }
}
```

